<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">station</ENAMEX> has been named <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Piazzale dei Partigiani</ENAMEX> .
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Luigi Einaudi</ENAMEX>, the <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">patriarch</ENAMEX> of postwar <ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">Italian</ENAMEX> politics,
<ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">President</ENAMEX> of the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Republic</ENAMEX> from <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1948 to 1955</TIMEX>,
when he was an octogenarian, has the unusual honor
of a street named for him in the heart of the <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC">city</ENAMEX>,
