            The use of the appositive to elevate appears to
be a commercial manifestation of titular colonicity,
the phenomenon noted first by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">J.T. Dillon</ENAMEX> in
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1981</TIMEX>.  The phrase refers, of course to the use of
