a corpus.  He demonstrates his point through a comparison
of <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">three</NUMEX> fields: literature, psychology, and
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">education</ENAMEX> and their increasing use of colons in titles
in <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">the 1970s and 1980s</TIMEX>.  Literature led the way but
the other fields have caught up.  <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Dillon</ENAMEX>'s article is a
masterly socio-graphic analysis.

