            In the Gaelic parts of <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Scotland</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Ireland</ENAMEX>, the
word for heather was fraoch , pronounced nearly like
<ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">German</ENAMEX> fr√∂ch .  There are many regional differences
in Gaelic, and fraoch can be pronounced ‚ÄúFREWX‚Äù or
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">‚ÄúFRAWX‚Äù</ENAMEX> in some parts of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Gaeldom</ENAMEX>, perhaps explaining
